Hello everyone, Iâ€™m SLS. Iâ€™ve got some important things to tell you today, itâ€™s about the adjustment of the directions of our channel. From now on, Iâ€™m no longer doing the weekly uploading anymore.

As you all know, Iâ€™ve been uploading videos every Friday night since 4, 5 years ago and never had any absence. And as time goes by, as I keep telling myself to become better, the productions of SLSMusic went more complicated and more professional. Thatâ€™s actually kind of a crazy achievement, and Iâ€™m very proud of it as well.

But just like many other creators may encountered, pressure and anxiety gradually invaded me. All that numbers, the views, likes, subscribers, I thought I handled all the stress pretty well, but the fact is that, unconsciously the negative energy still affected me mentally. Plus the recent COVID-19 thing, I often felt upset and powerless. In the meantime, I just kept chasing the latest anisong and  hit songs, being kidnapped by the algorithm, and ignore these potential issues,  I just wanted to be better, to do better, to serve more amazing music for my audience. I realized that Iâ€™ve somehow lost a little bit of myself.

After a period of self-examination, Iâ€™ve made my decision. Itâ€™s time to make some change this year. Instead of regularly uploading videos weekly, Iâ€™ll be more focus on the music, the production and the performance. More importantly, Iâ€™m going to go back to where I started, to make content whatever I want to make, not only anime, but anything I think itâ€™s worth sharing with you. And thatâ€™s really the reason I started with SLSMusic.

Donâ€™t worry, Iâ€™m not gonna stop updating. The regular livestream will still go on as well. Moreover, Iâ€™m gonna share more music with you, more exclusive contents (patreon/membership), and also, more of myself. Iâ€™m really excited. More stuff coming soon, follow me on YT/IG/Twitter/FB make sure you donâ€™t miss it!

I really wanna say a big THANKS to fans who support SLSMusic all these years, that really means a lot to me. Iâ€™m also glad my music could be a positive part of your life. Itâ€™s you who encourage me to keep fighting. Thank you so much. And for this new chapter, letâ€™s  continue our journey and make it more splendid.
